00:40:30,607 --> 00:40:34,142
He's getting on her nerves.
She's getting on his nerves.

644
00:40:34,361 --> 00:40:38,525
- Jesus! Where the hell are we?
- All right, take it easy.

645
00:40:38,657 --> 00:40:42,275
Don't tell me to take it easy, because
I've had enough already today.

646
00:40:42,411 --> 00:40:45,115
I'm a personal manager. I got
a big night ahead of me.

647
00:40:45,247 --> 00:40:48,164
Meanwhile I'm wandering
around here in North Vietnam.

648
00:40:48,292 --> 00:40:51,625
- We got away, didn't we?
- I got nothing to get away from.

649
00:40:51,753 --> 00:40:53,793
I didn't do anything.

650
00:40:53,922 --> 00:40:58,086
I'm running all of a sudden with
fortune-tellers and meat hooks.

651
00:40:58,218 --> 00:41:00,840
I'll take care of it
when we hit a phone.

652
00:41:00,971 --> 00:41:04,885
A phone? We're in a swamp, darling.
Where is there gonna be a phone here?

653
00:41:05,017 --> 00:41:07,305
She's with Lou and they
wanna break my legs.

654
00:41:07,436 --> 00:41:10,721
- I don't have to go tonight.
- Well, that's fine with me.

655
00:41:10,856 --> 00:41:13,773
Then don't, because I'm too
scared already anyhow.

656
00:41:13,901 --> 00:41:18,397
Lou, I wish you wouldn't drink like that.
You've got an important show tonight.

657
00:41:18,530 --> 00:41:21,650
I got a cold sore tonight.
Look at this thing over here.

658
00:41:21,783 --> 00:41:25,235
- It's nothing.
- It's gotta be tonight. Believe you me.

659
00:41:25,370 --> 00:41:28,537
And those TV people, they notice
everything. They're pros.

660
00:41:28,665 --> 00:41:31,583
- They got it down to a science.
- Turn on the ball game.

661
00:41:31,710 --> 00:41:35,161
I can't even decide whether to go
with "Boulevard of Broken Dreams"...

662
00:41:35,297 --> 00:41:37,835
or "Three Coins in the
Fountain" as an encore.

663
00:41:37,966 --> 00:41:42,545
The kids are driving me nuts over
here. Give me a break over here.

664
00:41:42,679 --> 00:41:46,594
I wonder where Danny is. I'm waiting
for his call. I got a million questions.

665
00:41:46,725 --> 00:41:50,176
- Where is Danny?
- Went to pick up his date in Jersey.

666
00:41:50,312 --> 00:41:52,850
I guess they probably
got tied up in traffic.

667
00:41:52,981 --> 00:41:56,148
- Who's his date?
- How do I know? Some broad.

668
00:41:56,818 --> 00:42:01,030
- Jesus. We're in the middle of nowhere.
- I never saw so many reeds in my life.

669
00:42:01,156 --> 00:42:04,027
- I feel like Moses.
- Lou's probably worried sick.

670
00:42:04,159 --> 00:42:08,786
Lou is probably drinking out of the
promotional-size whisky bottle by now.

671
00:42:08,914 --> 00:42:12,532
Hey, wait a minute. I know where
we are. These are the flatlands.

672
00:42:12,668 --> 00:42:15,123
My husband's friends used
to dump bodies here.

673
00:42:15,254 --> 00:42:18,705
Great. I'm sure you can show me all
the points of cultural interest.

674
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:21,378
Hey, who are you?

675
00:42:21,510 --> 00:42:23,384
Who are you?

676
00:42:23,512 --> 00:42:27,510
- Who are you?
- We're lost.

677
00:42:27,641 --> 00:42:30,642
We're shooting a commercial
down by the river.

678
00:42:30,769 --> 00:42:33,260
Fantastic! Unbelievable!

679
00:42:33,397 --> 00:42:37,477
What a break! I'm Danny Rose,
theatrical management. God bless you.

680
00:42:37,609 --> 00:42:39,898
- This is Tina...
- Vitale.

681
00:42:40,028 --> 00:42:43,528
Hi. I'm Ray Webb, the actor.
How you doin', babe?

682
00:42:43,657 --> 00:42:46,278
Listen, we gotta get a car.
Is it possible?

683
00:42:46,410 --> 00:42:50,277
- There are no cars out here till tonight.
- We need one now. It's an emergency.

684
00:42:50,414 --> 00:42:55,491
I'm a theatrical manager, so I gotta see
Berle at the Waldorf later. Milton Berle.

685
00:42:55,627 --> 00:43:00,123
There's a guy there with a boat. Give him
a couple of bucks. He'll take you across.

686
00:43:00,257 --> 00:43:02,582
- Great, great.
- I don't travel by water.

687
00:43:02,718 --> 00:43:05,505
It's against my religion.
I'm a landlocked Hebrew.

688
00:43:05,637 --> 00:43:09,421
You ever seen me on TV? I play the
shaving-cream man from outer space.

689
00:43:09,558 --> 00:43:11,847
- Wanna feel my cheeks, huh?
- Funny.

690
00:43:11,977 --> 00:43:15,678
Come on, Danny. We gotta take
this boat. Lou's waitin'. Come on.

691
00:43:15,814 --> 00:43:18,103
Five minutes across
the Hudson. It's nothin'.

692
00:43:18,233 --> 00:43:20,938
You want me to go on the
Hudson River? That's crazy!

693
00:43:21,069 --> 00:43:23,311
How did you two get out
here without a car?

694
00:43:23,447 --> 00:43:26,116
I've been through thick
and thin with that car.

695
00:43:26,241 --> 00:43:29,776
- Now I gotta leave it overnight?
- Pick it up tomorrow. It'll be fine.

696
00:43:29,912 --> 00:43:34,158
If anything happens to that car, I'll
be furious, Tina. I will be furious.

697
00:43:42,215 --> 00:43:45,916
<i>OK. Now they're gonna go
back to Manhattan by boat.</i>

698
00:43:46,053 --> 00:43:47,761
<i>A boat, mind you.</i>

699
00:43:47,888 --> 00:43:52,514
<i>Can you picture Danny Rose on a boat?
I mean, this guy is strictly pavement.</i>

700
00:43:52,643 --> 00:43:56,771
<i>He needs the smell of carbon
monoxide and litter to feel good.</i>

701
00:43:56,897 --> 00:43:59,602
<i>Danny is not meant for water.</i>

702
00:43:59,733 --> 00:44:03,731
<i>So, naturally, the minute he
steps on the boat, he's gone.</i>

703
00:44:03,862 --> 00:44:08,074
<i>A lunch he ate in 1956 is
beginning to come up on him.</i>

704
00:44:08,200 --> 00:44:10,027
<i>He's green. He's dizzy.</i>

705
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:14,739
<i>Tina's fine. She's made of steel. I'll
tell you what's going through her mind.</i>

706
00:44:14,873 --> 00:44:19,250
<i>She's thinking of a conversation
that she and Lou had a week before.</i>

707
00:44:20,295 --> 00:44:22,965
- Hey, hey! All right!
- Listen, Lou...

708
00:44:23,090 --> 00:44:28,084
I don't want you to break up with
your wife because of me. I don't...

709
00:44:28,220 --> 00:44:30,841
Tina, it's not you. This
has been on my mind.

710
00:44:30,973 --> 00:44:34,591
I'd feel like a home-wrecker.
That's what I feel like.

711
00:44:34,726 --> 00:44:36,933
I gotta change my whole lifestyle.

712
00:44:37,062 --> 00:44:41,012
The thing you gotta change
is your management.

713
00:44:41,149 --> 00:44:45,396
Listen, Danny's all right. So he's no
world-beater. I mean, he's all right.

714
00:44:45,529 --> 00:44:49,990
I know nothin' about show business.
And I got nothin' against the guy...

715
00:44:50,117 --> 00:44:53,450
but I see the joints you work
and the way things are going.

716
00:44:53,579 --> 00:44:55,701
You're better than
all these new guys.

717
00:44:55,831 --> 00:44:58,867
- You're prejudiced cos you like me.
- Yeah, sure I am.

718
00:44:59,001 --> 00:45:02,701
Listen, Danny'd be lost
without me. He's countin' on me.

719
00:45:02,838 --> 00:45:04,712
You know what you're doin'.

720
00:45:04,840 --> 00:45:07,413
Why don't you let me introduce
you to Sid Bacharach?

721
00:45:07,551 --> 00:45:10,220
How do you know him? Why
would he give me his time?

722
00:45:10,345 --> 00:45:14,557
He was good friends with my husband. They
were both very tight in Atlantic City.

723
00:45:14,683 --> 00:45:17,304
- Sid Bacharach, huh?
- He's a big guy, right?

724
00:45:17,436 --> 00:45:19,927
Big gun, big gun.
No two ways about it.

725
00:45:20,939 --> 00:45:24,189
<i>OK. Now they're in the
middle of the Hudson River.</i>

726
00:45:24,318 --> 00:45:28,232
<i>The fog has come in. Danny's face is...
what colour should I say?</i>

727
00:45:28,363 --> 00:45:30,937
<i>It's khaki. The man
has a khaki face.</i>

728
00:45:31,074 --> 00:45:34,574
<i>So Tina wanted Lou to leave Danny
and go with Sid Bacharach?</i>

729
00:45:34,703 --> 00:45:37,989
<i>That's exactly what I'm saying.
See, three days earlier...</i>

730
00:45:38,123 --> 00:45:42,203
<i>Tina had set up a secret lunch meeting
at some steak joint in Manhattan.</i>

731
00:45:42,336 --> 00:45:45,954
Well, guys, we finally made it.
Lou Canova, Sid Bacharach.

732
00:45:46,089 --> 00:45:49,541
- Sid, this is Lou.
- A pleasure, Mr Bacharach. Truly.

733
00:45:49,676 --> 00:45:52,677
I've only heard wonderful
things about you from Tina.

734
00:45:52,804 --> 00:45:56,387
- She does that all the time.
- No. You remember Lou from the '50s.

735
00:45:56,516 --> 00:45:59,802
- He's got it.
- I remember "Tossin' and Turnin'".

736
00:45:59,937 --> 00:46:02,309
That thing on "Perfidia" too.

737
00:46:02,439 --> 00:46:05,357
Now I understand you already
have representation.

738
00:46:05,484 --> 00:46:09,316
He's loyal to a guy who means well
but he can't seem to move him.

739
00:46:09,446 --> 00:46:11,273
I know all about those things...

740
00:46:11,406 --> 00:46:15,107
and sometimes it just doesn't
work out and he can't help you.

741
00:46:15,244 --> 00:46:18,992
It's my career. It's my life.
I gotta do what's right for it.

742
00:46:19,122 --> 00:46:23,500
I really wanna catch your act. I know this
nostalgia thing is really coming on strong.

743
00:46:23,627 --> 00:46:26,711
- He's hot now.
- I'm gonna be at the Waldorf on the 25th.

744
00:46:26,838 --> 00:46:29,875
25th. Be great if you could
come, Sid. He's ready.

745
00:46:30,008 --> 00:46:33,543
All he needs is somebody with a
little clout to open some doors.

746
00:46:33,679 --> 00:46:36,134
I'll do my best to make
it on Sunday night.

747
00:46:36,265 --> 00:46:38,934
Don't worry about it.
I'll get you in the back.

748
00:46:39,059 --> 00:46:41,728
- You won't regret it.
- No problem.

749
00:46:43,897 --> 00:46:49,188
<i>OK. So Tina's thinking about all this stuff
while they're sailing across the Hudson.</i>

750
00:46:49,319 --> 00:46:53,697
<i>Meanwhile, the two crazy brothers are
in New York looking to kill Danny.</i>

751
00:46:53,824 --> 00:46:57,109
<i>Wasn't Tina gonna make a phone
call and have 'em called off?</i>

752
00:46:57,244 --> 00:47:00,660
<i>She did, the minute they got
ashore, but it didn't work.</i>

753
00:47:00,789 --> 00:47:04,490
- So what's happening?
- You're gonna have to lay low for a while.

754
00:47:04,626 --> 00:47:07,746
- What do you mean?
- You got any friends outta town?

755
00:47:07,879 --> 00:47:11,462
- Outta town? Like where? Are you nuts?
- You better check into a hotel.

756
00:47:11,592 --> 00:47:13,964
You were gonna settle
this with one phone call.

757
00:47:14,094 --> 00:47:17,677
It's gonna take a few days.
Meanwhile, they're looking for you.

758
00:47:17,806 --> 00:47:20,842
Darling, can I say one thing?
I'm going to the police.

759
00:47:20,976 --> 00:47:23,514
No, that's a mistake.
You gotta lay low.

760
00:47:23,645 --> 00:47:28,936
Lay low? I didn't do anything! My whole
life I never got involved in any trouble.

761
00:47:29,067 --> 00:47:33,528
I eat the right foods. Now I gotta lay low?
Jesus! You said one phone call.

762
00:47:33,655 --> 00:47:36,858
I know. It's gonna be taken care of.
I got someone onto it.

763
00:47:36,992 --> 00:47:40,112
- My advice is to check into a hotel.
- I got an apartment.

764
00:47:40,245 --> 00:47:43,412
- Why do I need a hotel?
- You can't go back there for a few days.

765
00:47:43,540 --> 00:47:46,624
I'm gonna spend for a hotel while
I'm carrying an apartment?

766
00:47:46,752 --> 00:47:49,836
All right, it's a mix-up.
Just don't go home, that's all.

767
00:47:49,963 --> 00:47:53,379
I gotta go home. You know,
you're bad news, honey.

768
00:47:53,508 --> 00:47:56,426
I knew that when you were starting
with the ice pick on Lou.

769
00:47:56,553 --> 00:47:59,305
Nice girls don't screw
around with ice picks.

770
00:47:59,431 --> 00:48:01,554
- Just don't go home.
- I gotta go home.

771
00:48:01,683 --> 00:48:06,511
I gotta get my pills and my shorts. And
Lou, the poor guy, he's probably a wreck.

772
00:48:09,149 --> 00:48:13,017
I'm not drunk. I'm not drunk.

773
00:48:13,153 --> 00:48:15,193
I mean, I'm OK.

774
00:48:16,406 --> 00:48:18,980
I'm gonna be all right.

775
00:48:19,117 --> 00:48:22,652
Now where you been?
I'm goin' crazy. Where's Tina?

776
00:48:22,788 --> 00:48:28,493
Lou, Lou, take some black coffee and
get over to the Waldorf. She's here.

777
00:48:28,627 --> 00:48:31,628
You speak to him, cos he's lost.
He's gone already.

778
00:48:31,755 --> 00:48:34,756
Lou, I'll be there, honey.
Just do what Danny says.

779
00:48:34,883 --> 00:48:37,920
- Be nice to him.
- We'll meet you at the place.

780
00:48:38,053 --> 00:48:42,181
Of course I miss you. But will you
lay off the sauce? All right.

781
00:48:42,766 --> 00:48:45,637
He's drunk. I knew
this was gonna happen.

782
00:48:45,769 --> 00:48:49,470
Where are my pills? I need a
Valium the size of a hockey puck.

783
00:48:49,606 --> 00:48:53,438
- Who's this? Who is this here?
- What do you mean? That's Frank.

784
00:48:53,569 --> 00:48:56,273
Frank, Tony Bennett and me.
This was a big night.

785
00:48:56,405 --> 00:49:00,782
See me up there? A little tiny smudge
that's like a fingerprint. That's my head.

786
00:49:00,909 --> 00:49:04,824
There I am with Miss Judy Garland.
Never a dearer woman existed.

787
00:49:04,955 --> 00:49:07,956
- Where are you?
- Well, I'm right outside of frame.

788
00:49:08,083 --> 00:49:12,081
Cos if the picture went on another inch,
I would be... I was back behind the dais.

789
00:49:12,212 --> 00:49:16,506
And here's Mr Myron Cohen and...
Jesus, where is my bottle of pills?

790
00:49:16,633 --> 00:49:21,260
- How long have you had this joint?
- Joint? This is rent-controlled.

791
00:49:21,388 --> 00:49:25,053
You oughta fix it up.
You're living like a loser.

792
00:49:25,183 --> 00:49:27,390
Nobody ever comes over,
so what do I care?

793
00:49:27,519 --> 00:49:30,390
Nobody comes over?
You ever been married?

794
00:49:30,522 --> 00:49:32,978
No. I was engaged once
to a dancer, you know...

795
00:49:33,108 --> 00:49:37,521
but she ran away with a piano
player and I broke off with her.

796
00:49:37,654 --> 00:49:39,943
- You know what I'd do with this room?
- What?

797
00:49:40,073 --> 00:49:44,534
Liven it up. Do it all in somethin'
up, you know. Pink, maybe?

798
00:49:44,661 --> 00:49:47,615
- Pink?
- Yeah. You know, you gotta lighten it up.

799
00:49:47,748 --> 00:49:52,908
Pink with maybe some gold wallpaper.
And you need fabric, you know.

800
00:49:53,045 --> 00:49:57,089
Like big purple pillows or somethin'.
Maybe some incense.

801
00:49:57,215 --> 00:49:59,967
What is this? A Turkish
whorehouse? I live here.

802
00:50:00,093 --> 00:50:05,468
I'm serious. You gotta lighten it up.
Maybe some bamboo furniture. Bamboo.

803
00:50:05,599 --> 00:50:09,383
I always wanted to do a room in
bamboo with, like, zebra skins.

804
00:50:09,519 --> 00:50:12,307
- Really? Are you serious?
- Why not? It's exciting.

805
00:50:12,439 --> 00:50:16,353
What you're talking about is
like a tropical motif, right?

806
00:50:16,485 --> 00:50:20,103
- It's funny, cos actually I like bamboo.
- Really?

807
00:50:20,239 --> 00:50:24,236
Picture, like, hanging plants maybe,
and a really nice tile floor.

808
00:50:24,368 --> 00:50:27,618
Bamboo furniture. It's very
beautiful and very dramatic.

809
00:50:27,746 --> 00:50:30,533
- You got an eye for drama.
- You really think so?

810
00:50:30,666 --> 00:50:32,457
You sound surprised.

811
00:50:32,584 --> 00:50:36,000
Nobody ever liked my
African-jungle idea before.

812
00:50:36,129 --> 00:50:39,913
I always had this as a dream.
You're the first person ever liked it.

813
00:50:40,050 --> 00:50:44,214
I'm willing to bet that you're full of
good ideas, but you lack confidence.

814
00:50:44,346 --> 00:50:48,344
- You don't have any confidence.
- It's my big problem as a decorator.

815
00:50:48,475 --> 00:50:53,517
Sure, it's like the acts I handle. I could
straighten you out in no time at all.

816
00:50:53,647 --> 00:50:58,558
Cos I don't see you just decorating little
joints and little apartments in the suburbs.

817
00:50:58,694 --> 00:51:02,110
I see you doing your gold walls
and your Turkish pillows...

818
00:51:02,239 --> 00:51:05,822
and all that garbage in hotels
and embassies and stuff.

819
00:51:05,951 --> 00:51:07,908
- Really?
- Yeah, naturally.

820
00:51:08,036 --> 00:51:10,788
- You could. I can smell it.
- I don't think so.

821
00:51:10,914 --> 00:51:14,829
The boat's sailed for me. I should have
been more serious when I was younger.

822
00:51:14,960 --> 00:51:17,712
Younger? You got your
whole life ahead of you.

823
00:51:17,838 --> 00:51:21,456
The trouble is I look at my
work and I think it's ugly.

824
00:51:21,592 --> 00:51:25,292
Well, my uncle Morris, the
famous diabetic from Brooklyn...

825
00:51:25,429 --> 00:51:28,762
used to say "If you hate yourself,
then you hate your work."

826
00:51:28,891 --> 00:51:31,808
I sleep at night. It's you
that's got the ulcer.

827
00:51:31,935 --> 00:51:36,396
I got an ulcer, but it may be a good thing.
You know what my philosophy of life is?

828
00:51:36,523 --> 00:51:40,735
That it's important to have some laughs,
but you gotta suffer a little too...

829
00:51:40,861 --> 00:51:44,111
because otherwise you miss
the whole point to life.

830
00:51:44,239 --> 00:51:46,813
- Know what my philosophy of life is?
- I can imagine.

831
00:51:46,950 --> 00:51:50,568
It's over quick, so have a good time.
You see want you want, go for it.

832
00:51:50,704 --> 00:51:55,745
Don't pay attention to anyone else. Do it to
the other guy first, or he'll do it to you.

833
00:51:55,876 --> 00:52:01,001
This is a philosophy of life? It sounds like
the screenplay to "Murder Incorporated".

834
00:52:01,131 --> 00:52:04,547
Hold this. That's ridiculous. No
wonder you don't like yourself.

