01:07:53,458 --> 01:07:57,705
- Yeah? Like what?
- Tina and I, we're crazy about each other.

1048
01:07:57,838 --> 01:08:00,411
And I feel I gotta say
something to Terry about it.

1049
01:08:00,549 --> 01:08:05,092
If that's what you decide on, that's what
you do. If you gotta do it, you gotta do it.

1050
01:08:05,220 --> 01:08:09,929
- I just hope you know what you're doing.
- We're sure about a lot of things.

1051
01:08:10,058 --> 01:08:12,728
I feel for myself that I gotta
make a few changes.

1052
01:08:12,853 --> 01:08:15,723
- What kind of changes?
- Like management.

1053
01:08:17,357 --> 01:08:19,397
What do you mean, management?

1054
01:08:20,360 --> 01:08:22,436
What do you mean, management?

1055
01:08:22,571 --> 01:08:26,699
Tina's really close to Sid Bacharach.
You had to notice him there tonight.

1056
01:08:26,825 --> 01:08:29,281
He was there to see me.

1057
01:08:32,122 --> 01:08:35,456
I don't understand. You
wanna change management?

1058
01:08:36,501 --> 01:08:41,662
Don't think it's not hard for me to say,
but I gotta do what's right for my career.

1059
01:08:43,508 --> 01:08:47,672
What do you mean? Am I hear...?
I can't believe you're saying this.

1060
01:08:47,804 --> 01:08:52,763
Danny, Sid can really move me.
I mean, we've got this special rapport.

1061
01:08:54,770 --> 01:08:59,479
How do you know Sid? Have you been
pushing him to... to leave me?

1062
01:08:59,608 --> 01:09:04,436
Hey, leave me outta this. All I know is
he's a big talent and he's playin' joints.

1063
01:09:04,571 --> 01:09:06,896
Joints? He was lucky
he could get j...

1064
01:09:07,032 --> 01:09:10,864
When I met him, he was still
singing "Funiculì Funiculà".

1065
01:09:10,994 --> 01:09:15,206
- Look, Danny, facts are facts.
- What are you talking about?

1066
01:09:15,332 --> 01:09:19,033
- This kid owes me his life.
- Leave her outta it. What's done is done.

1067
01:09:19,169 --> 01:09:22,004
I don't understand you, Lou.
We've been through so much.

1068
01:09:22,130 --> 01:09:25,416
You make everything into
a personal situation.

1069
01:09:25,551 --> 01:09:29,133
Of course I make it personal.
That's our relationship.

1070
01:09:29,263 --> 01:09:32,513
You can't put into a
contract what I do with you.

1071
01:09:32,641 --> 01:09:35,512
Can I give you...? My uncle
Meyer, the man sold apples...

1072
01:09:35,644 --> 01:09:38,811
- Say somethin'. You know I'm not verbal.
- This is between you.

1073
01:09:38,939 --> 01:09:42,889
You gotta do what you gotta do
and Danny's gotta understand it.

1074
01:09:43,026 --> 01:09:47,569
Danny, if anything comes outta this, you
know you're gonna be in for a taste.

1075
01:09:47,698 --> 01:09:53,072
Danny. Where you goin',
Danny? Danny. Danny.

1076
01:10:00,210 --> 01:10:03,745
Hey, how you doin', Danny?
You hear about Barney Dunn?

1077
01:10:03,880 --> 01:10:08,626
Couple of guys done a pretty good job
on him. They beat him up pretty badly.

1078
01:10:10,721 --> 01:10:14,765
- I thought he was on a cruise.
- Nah, nah, that was cancelled.

1079
01:10:14,892 --> 01:10:18,011
He's in the hospital now. It
was pretty rough for a while.

1080
01:10:18,145 --> 01:10:21,146
It was touch and go.
But it's all right now.

1081
01:10:21,273 --> 01:10:25,401
The cops got 'em. They got the
guys that done the job on him.

1082
01:10:26,695 --> 01:10:29,151
- Which hospital?
- Roosevelt.

1083
01:11:03,148 --> 01:11:05,188
How you doin', Barney?

1084
01:11:07,110 --> 01:11:10,195
Danny. Wh-wh-what
are you doing here?

1085
01:11:11,156 --> 01:11:15,284
Well, I heard that you
got beat up, so...

1086
01:11:16,828 --> 01:11:20,612
I s-s-still don't
know what happened.

1087
01:11:20,749 --> 01:11:24,663
I want you to know if there's
anything I can do, anything at all.

1088
01:11:24,795 --> 01:11:27,831
Hospital bills, anything at
all, I'll take care of it.

1089
01:11:27,965 --> 01:11:30,669
You wanna pay my hospital bills?

1090
01:11:30,801 --> 01:11:33,339
Danny, are you sure <i>you're</i> OK?

1091
01:11:33,470 --> 01:11:36,969
Really, Barney, anything at all.
Whatever you need.

1092
01:11:55,742 --> 01:11:58,280
I thought this was a
funny story. It's terrible.

1093
01:11:58,412 --> 01:12:00,654
What do you want me to do?
It's not <i>my</i> life.

1094
01:12:00,789 --> 01:12:04,324
So Lou leaves his wife and kids
and he moves in with Tina.

1095
01:12:04,459 --> 01:12:08,160
<i>Sid Bacharach's handling him.
He's doin' all right.</i>

1096
01:12:09,006 --> 01:12:11,960
<i>♪ The world and all of its gold</i>

1097
01:12:12,092 --> 01:12:15,959
<i>♪ Oh, gold won't
bring you happiness</i>

1098
01:12:16,471 --> 01:12:18,962
<i>♪ When you're growing old</i>

1099
01:12:19,099 --> 01:12:22,053
<i>♪ Oh, the world,
it's still the same</i>

1100
01:12:22,185 --> 01:12:24,344
You OK? You seem a little down.

1101
01:12:24,479 --> 01:12:26,935
No. I have a headache.

1102
01:12:27,900 --> 01:12:30,437
What are you giving me?
I ordered a Courvoisier.

1103
01:12:30,569 --> 01:12:34,863
- Didn't you order a Jack Daniels?
- I ordered a Courvoisier.

1104
01:12:34,990 --> 01:12:39,533
- You did say Courvoisier.
- Let's not make a federal case out of it.

1105
01:12:44,541 --> 01:12:49,203
- Honey, what are you doin' up?
- I can't sleep.

1106
01:12:49,338 --> 01:12:53,170
- It's four o'clock in the morning.
- Yeah, I know. I had a bad dream.

1107
01:12:53,300 --> 01:12:57,463
Is this like a thing or somethin'?
This is goin' on every other night.

1108
01:12:57,596 --> 01:13:00,763
- Why don't you take a pill or somethin'?
- I don't like pills.

1109
01:13:00,891 --> 01:13:04,260
When I can't sleep, I take one of
those Seconals. I go out like a baby.

1110
01:13:04,394 --> 01:13:07,977
- I'm OK. I'm fine.
- Listen, I got a great new idea.

1111
01:13:08,106 --> 01:13:13,148
In Atlantic City, I'll open up with
"You're Nobody Till Somebody Loves You".

1112
01:13:13,278 --> 01:13:15,318
Then I'll go into
"When You're Smiling".

1113
01:13:15,447 --> 01:13:19,231
- Give me a break. It's four in the morning.
- You're not listening to me.

1114
01:13:19,368 --> 01:13:21,360
This is important stuff.

1115
01:13:22,246 --> 01:13:26,374
Angelina, I can't sleep.
I... I feel jumpy.

1116
01:13:27,626 --> 01:13:30,199
I don't know. I'm not myself.

1117
01:13:31,463 --> 01:13:33,919
I see bad dreams.

1118
01:13:34,800 --> 01:13:38,251
Deep dreams. Bad conscience.

1119
01:13:38,387 --> 01:13:42,384
Yeah. A little while
ago I met some man.

1120
01:13:42,516 --> 01:13:44,841
I hardly spent any time with him.

1121
01:13:44,977 --> 01:13:48,143
One day we had an adventure.

1122
01:13:48,272 --> 01:13:51,771
Yes. He makes you feel uneasy.

1123
01:13:51,900 --> 01:13:57,143
I did him some... some little wrong.
Just some small business matter.

1124
01:13:57,281 --> 01:13:59,688
I didn't even know him very well.

1125
01:13:59,825 --> 01:14:06,362
When I had the chance to say
something, I... I didn't speak up.

1126
01:14:06,832 --> 01:14:09,619
I have a vision of you...

1127
01:14:09,751 --> 01:14:12,325
standing before a large mirror.

1128
01:14:13,046 --> 01:14:15,798
I... I had that dream last week.

1129
01:14:15,924 --> 01:14:18,047
That was it, exactly my dream.

1130
01:14:18,176 --> 01:14:20,846
What is it you're seeking there?

1131
01:14:23,098 --> 01:14:25,636
I wanna rest easy again.

1132
01:14:25,767 --> 01:14:28,223
I wanna find myself.

1133
01:14:29,062 --> 01:14:32,312
I wanna wipe out my thoughts
and forget this guy.

1134
01:14:33,317 --> 01:14:37,266
I can't see clearly. It's unclear.

1135
01:14:37,404 --> 01:14:39,693
It's all unclear.

1136
01:14:39,823 --> 01:14:42,610
<i>Non ci vedo bene. Non é chiaro.</i>

1137
01:14:44,328 --> 01:14:47,364
What's the matter with you lately?
You're so edgy.

1138
01:14:47,497 --> 01:14:51,080
I don't wanna go to California, OK?
It gives me the creeps out there.

1139
01:14:51,209 --> 01:14:55,753
- It's important you go to California.
- Well, then you go.

1140
01:14:55,881 --> 01:14:59,499
What is it with you? Lately
everything's goin' so nicely.

1141
01:14:59,635 --> 01:15:03,928
My comeback's in full swing now.
But you weren't happy in Vegas.

1142
01:15:04,056 --> 01:15:07,970
You weren't happy in Atlantic City.
I thought you'd be happy.

1143
01:15:08,101 --> 01:15:11,138
I'm moody. You knew I was
moody when you met me.

1144
01:15:11,271 --> 01:15:15,565
I had it with the moods. I gotta
go to California, that's it.

1145
01:15:15,692 --> 01:15:18,148
Honey, what's the matter?

1146
01:15:19,613 --> 01:15:21,652
I don't know.

1147
01:15:24,868 --> 01:15:26,612
<i>Lou moves to LA.</i>

1148
01:15:26,745 --> 01:15:30,909
<i>Tina doesn't. It's all over between 'em.
Guess who calls her for a date.</i>

1149
01:15:31,041 --> 01:15:33,912
- <i>I have no idea.</i>
- <i>Remember the shaving-cream man?</i>

1150
01:15:34,044 --> 01:15:36,167
<i>The guy she met with
Danny in the reeds?</i>

1151
01:15:36,296 --> 01:15:40,164
<i>That's right. They start going out.
But she's just as moody with him.</i>

1152
01:15:40,300 --> 01:15:44,345
<i>They fight, they argue. Then one
morning... Thanksgiving morning</i>

1153
01:15:44,471 --> 01:15:46,796
<i>the two of them are
on Central Park West.</i>

1154
01:15:46,932 --> 01:15:48,971
<i>There's the parade.</i>

1155
01:16:44,114 --> 01:16:46,154
- Now what's wrong?
- I don't know.

1156
01:16:46,283 --> 01:16:48,821
Jesus, Tina, what's wrong with you?

1157
01:16:48,952 --> 01:16:53,448
Look, maybe we should have a little
heart-to-heart. Everything makes you cry.

1158
01:16:53,582 --> 01:16:57,033
Maybe you should see a doctor. I don't
know what to do with you. Baby!

1159
01:16:57,169 --> 01:16:59,126
What are you trying to pull here?

1160
01:16:59,880 --> 01:17:04,257
- I gotta see Angelina right away.
- I'm sorry. Angelina's not here.

1161
01:17:04,384 --> 01:17:06,922
What time's she coming back?
I need her advice.

1162
01:17:07,054 --> 01:17:10,838
She's with her grandchildren.
She won't be here until Monday.

1163
01:17:10,974 --> 01:17:14,474
- This is important.
- I can't help it if it's important.

1164
01:17:14,603 --> 01:17:18,303
She won't be here until Monday.
Please come Monday.

1165
01:17:34,790 --> 01:17:37,245
OK, I got the frozen turkeys!

1166
01:17:39,836 --> 01:17:43,170
- Thank you, Danny.
- Give me a little hand. God love you.

1167
01:17:43,298 --> 01:17:45,920
- Here's your frozen turkey.
- Thank you.

1168
01:17:46,051 --> 01:17:50,096
B- B-Believe me, the frozen is
just as g-good as the r-real.

1169
01:17:50,222 --> 01:17:51,550
- Got it?
- Uh-huh.

1170
01:17:51,682 --> 01:17:54,089
The frozens are much cheaper
than the real ones.

1171
01:17:54,226 --> 01:17:58,224
- Can I help?
- No, sit there. You'll fall over.

1172
01:17:58,355 --> 01:18:01,024
Just dig in, dig in.
Don't hesitate.

1173
01:18:02,067 --> 01:18:04,523
- This is really great.
- Would you like a drink?

1174
01:18:04,653 --> 01:18:06,859
I'd love it.

1175
01:18:06,989 --> 01:18:10,571
There's some Tab and
some club soda.

1176
01:18:10,701 --> 01:18:13,405
Give her some Coke.
Excuse me one second.

1177
01:18:13,537 --> 01:18:17,072
Hello? Yeah, sure.
We're... That's right.

1178
01:18:17,207 --> 01:18:20,244
It's the twins.
It's the twins. They're...

1179
01:18:22,045 --> 01:18:24,085
Sure, darling. Sure.

1180
01:18:24,214 --> 01:18:27,879
And the new noses are good?
Yes. Sure.

1181
01:18:34,182 --> 01:18:36,638
I... I came to apologise.

1182
01:18:42,441 --> 01:18:45,192
You gonna ask me in?

1183
01:18:45,319 --> 01:18:47,810
Let me call you back. Yeah.

1184
01:18:47,946 --> 01:18:51,647
I'll get back to you. Let me
call you. I'll call you back.

1185
01:18:54,286 --> 01:18:56,741
Hope I'm not intruding.

1186
01:19:01,710 --> 01:19:05,577
- I realise you hate me.
- Bring her in. The food's gettin' cold.

1187
01:19:05,714 --> 01:19:08,335
D- D-Danny,
who's your fr-fr-fr... guest?

1188
01:19:09,426 --> 01:19:12,095
Oh, it's nobody. It's nothing.

1189
01:19:14,306 --> 01:19:19,680
Was it your uncle Sidney who said
"acceptance, forgiveness and love"?

1190
01:19:19,811 --> 01:19:21,934
Look, I've had a bad year.

1191
01:19:22,064 --> 01:19:27,022
If things don't pick up for me, I'm
gonna be selling storm windows soon.

1192
01:19:28,487 --> 01:19:31,357
I'd like to be friends.

1193
01:19:31,490 --> 01:19:35,073
I don't think that would
be such a great idea.

1194
01:19:35,202 --> 01:19:38,618
This is the best Thanksgiving
party we've had so far!

1195
01:19:38,747 --> 01:19:40,823
Here's your napkin, honey.

1196
01:19:40,958 --> 01:19:43,449
This is absolutely the
best Thanksgiving party.

1197
01:19:43,585 --> 01:19:47,203
- Danny, this is marvellous.
- Danny, who's your fr-fr-fr... guest?

1198
01:19:47,339 --> 01:19:51,882
- The cranberry sauce is dry.
- You're eating the mashed potatoes.

1199
01:19:52,719 --> 01:19:55,175
Hey, what a spread!

1200
01:19:56,306 --> 01:20:01,182
Gloria, wait a second. Hey, Danny,
thanks a lot for the invite.

1201
01:20:01,311 --> 01:20:04,396
Thanksgiving sure
rolls around fast.

1202
01:21:03,332 --> 01:21:07,376
<i>- Well, that's my Danny Rose story.
- Unbelievable.</i>

1203
01:21:07,502 --> 01:21:11,251
<i>The man is a living legend. Do you
know that only six months ago...</i>

1204
01:21:11,381 --> 01:21:14,881
<i>they gave him the greatest honour
you can get in the Broadway area?</i>

1205
01:21:15,010 --> 01:21:19,257
<i>Look at the menu. At this delicatessen
they named a sandwich after him.</i>

1206
01:21:19,389 --> 01:21:21,762
<i>The Danny Rose Special.</i>

1207
01:21:21,892 --> 01:21:25,225
<i>Probably a cream cheese on a
bagel with marinara sauce.</i>

1208
01:21:25,354 --> 01:21:27,062
<i>He deserves it.</i>

1209
01:21:27,189 --> 01:21:29,976
<i>Did you ever go to one of
his Thanksgiving parties?</i>

1210
01:21:30,108 --> 01:21:31,271
<i>One party.</i>

1211
01:21:31,401 --> 01:21:34,272
<i>Where they have the frozen turkey.</i>

1212
01:21:34,404 --> 01:21:38,319
- <i>Economical, but a lot of laughs.</i>
- <i>Cranberry sauce made like a rocket.</i>

1213
01:21:38,450 --> 01:21:40,988
- <i>You had to de-thaw the corn.</i>
- <i>It was incredible.</i>

1214
01:21:41,119 --> 01:21:46,624
<i>Listen, excuse me. Before we go any
further, may I ask you a favour?</i>

1215
01:21:46,750 --> 01:21:49,075
<i>Can we go home now? I'm tired.</i>

1216
01:21:49,211 --> 01:21:50,373
<i>We're having laughs.</i>

1217
01:21:50,504 --> 01:21:52,081
<i>I haven't seen you in 110 years.</i>

1218
01:21:52,214 --> 01:21:53,922
<i>I'm going to Atlantic
City tomorrow.</i>

1219
01:21:54,049 --> 01:21:57,216
<i>- I'll get the check. I'll take care of it.
- Really?</i>

1220
01:21:57,344 --> 01:22:00,678
<i>National holiday.
Corbett has the check.</i>

1221
01:22:00,806 --> 01:22:03,475
<i>For these kind of laughs,
I figure it's worth it.</i>

1222
01:22:03,600 --> 01:22:05,759
<i>Well, we'll do it again tomorrow.</i>

1223
01:24:13,647 --> 01:24:16,731
Visiontext Subtitles: Sally Lewis